  "prompt": "What profitable business I can start with INR 1 lakh?",
  "response": "Starting a business with a budget of INR 1 lakh requires careful planning and strategic execution. Here are several business ideas that you might consider:\n\n1. **Freelancing Services**: If you have expertise in areas like graphic design, content writing, digital marketing, web development, or video editing, you can start a freelancing business. You can work from home, thus reducing overhead costs.\n\n2. **Tutoring or Online Coaching**: Use your skills to offer tutoring services in subjects you excel in or provide online coaching for competitive exams, language learning, or personal development.\n\n3. **Digital Products**: Create and sell digital products like e-books, online courses, or stock photos. You can leverage platforms like Udemy, Teachable, or Amazon Kindle to reach a global audience.\n\n4. **Home-based Bakery/Catering**: If you have a knack for cooking or baking, you could start a small-scale bakery or catering business from your home. Start with orders from friends and family and expand through word-of-mouth and social media marketing.\n\n5. **Handmade Crafts or Art**: If you are good at making crafts or art, you can sell your creations online through platforms like Etsy, Instagram, or even local marketplaces.\n\n6. **Dropshipping**: Start an online store without holding inventory. Find suppliers who manufacture and ship products directly to your customers. Investments will primarily go towards setting up your online store and marketing.\n\n7. **Pet Services**: Offer pet grooming, walking, or daycare services. The initial investment would be low, and you can operate from home or go to clients\u2019 homes.\n\n8. **Mobile/Computer Repair Services**: If you have technical skills, provide repair services for mobile devices or computers. Cost involves purchasing tools and equipment.\n\n9. **Stationery Supplies**: Start a small business selling stationery and office supplies. This can be done through a physical store or an online platform.\n\n10. **Event Planning**: Organize and manage small local events and parties. You can offer services for birthdays, anniversaries, and corporate events.\n\n11. **Fitness Training**: If you have experience in fitness, consider starting a personal training business or conducting fitness classes, like yoga or Zumba, at local community centers or parks.\n\n12. **Photography/Videography**: Start a photography or videography business. This may require investment in a good camera and related equipment.\n\nIt\u2019s crucial to conduct thorough market research and understand local demand for the services or products you wish to provide. Make a detailed business plan, keep recurring expenses low, and leverage digital marketing to reach a wider audience without substantial advertising costs.",
